('607', '100', 'content_ml_rich_text_english', 'After eating breakfast, several detainees reported attending a flag raising ceremony in the morning, where they were made to stand at attention in their cell or the hallway and listen to the national anthem.  Detainees spend a significant portion of the day singing ‘red’ songs. Songs are nearly always sung before breakfast and other meals, and often throughout the day, and often for hours on end, until their throats became sore from singing. The songs usually included the national anthem and other ‘red’ songs about the greatness of China, Chinese Communist Party, or Xi Jinping Detainees were punished for not singing and for singing the songs incorrectly.'),
