('1566', '140', 'content_ml_rich_text_english', 'After washing up and using the toilet, detainees have a small breakfast, which is either delivered in their cell through a hole in door or at the camp canteen. Many detainees reported that they were given very little to eat or drink, and had very little time to eat.  “They didn’t give us water at night. I was thirsty all the time. We got just half a cup [of water] at meals,” [Pseudonym] told Amnesty International.'),
